  "issue_title": "feature: add agent run detail screen",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\nThe chat timeline should stay compact, but maintainers and advanced users need a deeper view of a local agent run for debugging and live validation.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd an agent run detail screen that can be opened from a completed run or logs. It should show the full ordered step list, tool calls, redacted arguments, verification details, stop reason, and trace/export affordance if already supported.\n\n## User workflow\n\nA user or maintainer taps a run summary and inspects the full run details without digging through raw log text.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThis supports on-device debugging and trust in the local observe-decide-act loop.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nThe detail screen must use display-safe/redacted fields and should not expose raw accessibility snapshots unless the user explicitly exports a redacted debug trace.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Run detail screen is reachable from chat run summary or logs.\n- Shows ordered steps with statuses and timestamps.\n- Shows redacted tool args/results and verification details.\n- Provides a clear empty/error state if run data is unavailable.\n- Does not display raw sensitive screen text.",
